Dependencies
Note:
    when certificate checking of the https-host fails, wget can be used with option --no-check-certificates
    This is ugly and should not be done for a productive system but can be useful when trying to set up the
    testing environment.

    node
    npm
    mongodb (installed as explained on http://docs.mongodb.org/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/)
Note: When failing to get the GPG key from the keyserver directly (firewall issues maybe?) the key can be
    taken from this repository and added to the keychain using 'apt-key add mongodb-gpgkey'
